					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I think it means graphics matching those of the consoles that belonged in the 8-bit category in the console wars era (sega vs nintendo). Forget technical aspects, this is a cultural discussion. The consoles that were known as 8-bit were mainly the NES and the Sega Master System. So 8-bit graphics are graphics that look like (or at least how people remember them to be) the graphics in those console's games.</div>

					
